  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the funniest thing a kid has put on their test/homework?",
  "response": "Kids often have a unique and unfiltered perspective that leads to hilarious and unexpected responses on tests and homework. Here are some funny examples:\n\n1. **Math Test:**  \n   Q: \"If there are 3 apples and you take away 2, how many do you have?\"  \n   A: **\"2 apples. I took them. They're mine now.\"**\n\n2. **Science Homework:**  \n   Q: \"What is the boiling point of water?\"  \n   A: **\"Hot.\"**\n\n3. **Spelling Test:**  \n   Q: \"Spell 'because.'\"  \n   A: **\"Bikoz.\"**\n\n4. **History Assignment:**  \n   Q: \"Who was the first president of the United States?\"  \n   A: **\"George Washing Machine.\"**\n\n5. **Art Class:**  \n   Q: \"Draw something inspired by nature.\"  \n   A: *Kid draws a stick figure with a caption:* **\"This is a tree. It\u2019s naked.\"**\n\n6. **Geography Quiz:**  \n   Q: \"Name the capital of France.\"  \n   A: **\"F.\"**\n\n7. **Creative Writing:**  \n   Q: \"Write a sentence using the word 'imagination.'\"  \n   A: **\"I used my imagination to pretend I did my homework.\"**\n\n8. **Science Test:**  \n   Q: \"What is photosynthesis?\"  \n   A: **\"When plants take selfies with the sun.\"**\n\n9. **English Assignment:**  \n   Q: \"Use 'their,' 'there,' and 'they're' in a sentence.\"  \n   A: **\"Their there they\u2019re.\"**\n\n10. **Parent-Teacher Conference Comment:**  \n   Teacher: \"Your child wrote on their test, 'I hope you have a great day.'\"  \n   Parent: \"At least they\u2019re polite!\"\n\nKids\u2019 unfiltered creativity and logic never fail to bring a smile\u2014or a laugh\u2014to anyone reading their work!",
